{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/blog/laugh-off/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Developer's blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"7ff9b611-2b59-58dd-93d1-a0d9424ccdc4","excerpt":"Meaning To laugh off means to treat something (such as a problem, criticism, or an embarrassing situation) as unimportant by joking or laughing about it instead…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#meaning\">Meaning</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#grammar-and-usage\">Grammar and Usage</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#common-phrases\">Common Phrases</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#collocations\">Collocations</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#examples\">Examples</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#synonyms-or-related\">Synonyms or Related</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#antonym\">Antonym</a></li>\n</ul>","html":"<h2 id=\"meaning\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#meaning\" aria-label=\"meaning permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Meaning</h2>\n<p><em>To laugh off</em> means to treat something (such as a problem, criticism, or an embarrassing situation) as unimportant by joking or laughing about it instead of taking it seriously.</p>\n<h2 id=\"grammar-and-usage\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#grammar-and-usage\" aria-label=\"grammar and usage permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Grammar and Usage</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Part of speech</strong>: Phrasal verb</li>\n<li><strong>Pattern</strong>: <em>laugh sth off</em> (transitive)</li>\n<li>Used with an object (the thing being dismissed).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Example structure:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><em>laugh + object + off</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><em>She laughed the mistake off.</em></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"common-phrases\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#common-phrases\" aria-label=\"common phrases permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Common Phrases</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>laugh off criticism</strong></li>\n<li><strong>laugh off rumors</strong></li>\n<li><strong>laugh off embarrassment</strong></li>\n<li><strong>laugh off a mistake</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"collocations\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#collocations\" aria-label=\"collocations permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Collocations</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><em>laugh off an insult</em></li>\n<li><em>laugh off a problem</em></li>\n<li><em>laugh off concerns</em></li>\n<li><em>laugh off failure</em></li>\n<li><em>laugh off danger</em></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"examples\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#examples\" aria-label=\"examples permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Examples</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>He laughed off the criticism and kept doing what he loved.</li>\n<li>She tried to laugh off her mistake during the meeting.</li>\n<li>The actor laughed off the rumors about his private life.</li>\n<li>He laughed off the accident as if it had never happened.</li>\n<li>The manager laughed off the team’s concerns, but later took action.</li>\n<li>She laughed off the embarrassment of tripping on stage.</li>\n<li>He laughed off the insult instead of arguing back.</li>\n<li>They laughed off the rumors spreading on social media.</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"synonyms-or-related\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#synonyms-or-related\" aria-label=\"synonyms or related permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Synonyms or Related</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>brush off</li>\n<li>shrug off</li>\n<li>dismiss</li>\n<li>downplay</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"antonym\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#antonym\" aria-label=\"antonym permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Antonym</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>take seriously</li>\n<li>dwell on</li>\n<li>emphasize</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"laugh off meaning and examples","date":"2025-09-20","description":"English learning materials; laugh off explanation.","tags":["English","phrasal verbs"],"featuredImage":{"publicURL":"/static/55b8e8a083ed63723051bbab7449efd3/laugh-off.png","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#f8e8a8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/55b8e8a083ed63723051bbab7449efd3/b5658/laugh-off.png","srcSet":"/static/55b8e8a083ed63723051bbab7449efd3/acb7c/laugh-off.png 256w,\n/static/55b8e8a083ed63723051bbab7449efd3/ccc41/laugh-off.png 512w,\n/static/55b8e8a083ed63723051bbab7449efd3/b5658/laugh-off.png 1024w","sizes":"(min-width: 1024px) 1024px, 100vw"},"sources":[{"srcSet":"/static/55b8e8a083ed63723051bbab7449efd3/22bfc/laugh-off.webp 256w,\n/static/55b8e8a083ed63723051bbab7449efd3/d689f/laugh-off.webp 512w,\n/static/55b8e8a083ed63723051bbab7449efd3/67ded/laugh-off.webp 1024w","